-- China's CICC says chairman resigns, to be replaced by head of sovereign wealth fund
-- By David Lin and Engen Tham
-- Wed Oct 22, 2014 10:22PM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, Oct 23 (Reuters) - China International Capital Corp (CICC) said on Thursday its Chairman Jin Liqun resigned from his post and will be replaced by the head of the country's sovereign wealth fund.

China Investment Corporation's current Chairman and Chief Executive Ding Xuedong has been appointed as the new CICC chairman, the investment bank said in a statement.